description.0: What has caused Luke to fall into a coma?
description.3: How does Devil Dinosaur find himself in modern-day Nevada? It all begins when Moon-Boy and Devil pay a visit to the Hag of the Pits. Strange, psychedelic visions follow.
description.4: Johnny Blaze meets a mysterious psychic while lost in the desert.
description.5: A traitor at the Gamma Base is causing the devastating breakdown of General Ross. Plus, Hulk has an (unexpected) extraterrestrial adventure!
description.6: Spymaster kills Tony Stark with a sniper rifle.
description.7: Sword and sorcery...in space! The Lunatik 'invites' Man-Wolf to take up arms in the Other Realm's Otherwar!
description.8: Jerry Hunt has a terrifying encounter with the mind-manipulating Needle! Spider-Woman swoops in for the save.
description.9: Hela and the Forces of Darkness rise against Asgard! Thor must make a decision- live in the realm of the gods, or remain on Earth forever.
description.10: We know Bruce Banner became the irradiated being known as the Hulk, but what if young Rick Jones had absorbed the gamma rays instead? In a twist of fate, Bruce Banner fails to save Rick Jones from becoming a teenage Hulk!
description.11: With the construction of a massive citadel by the Sun-People threatening the ecosystem of the Savage Land, the X-Men have agreed to help Ka-Zar prevent destruction.
description.12: Pop the champagne- the Fantastic Four are back! But before they can get settled, the team is threatened by their own building! What's causing the Baxter Building to attack its own residents?
description.18: Kidnapped - by Kiber the Cruel! Held captive by enemy agents, T'Challa must use all his cunning to stage an escape and reach his cousin Khanata before it's too late!
description.20: Mar-Vell and Drax the Destroyer find nothing but complications on the planet Titan!
description.22: Daredevil infiltrates the Avengers mansion and confronts the Black Widow!
description.23: Devil and Moon-Boy attempt to find the Small-Folk tribe, but attract the attention of Riders. Moon-Boy is able to escape, but he must leave Devil behind! The Small-Folk are still cautious of Devil, but Moon-Boy assuages their fear.
description.24: The Hulk is provoked and attacked by Moonstone! But this villainess is also Dr. Karla Sofen, an esteemed associate of Doc Samson. Moonstone's origin revealed!
description.25: Iron Man goes toe to toe with the Ani-Men and is lead into a trap created by none other than Spymaster.
description.26: Will Loki escape captivity before his fate is sealed at the Place of Judgement? Meanwhile, Lady Sif lashes out at Red for his supposed 'power'.
description.27: Dracula has survived his son Janus...but will he survive against his daughter Lilith?!
description.28: Trying to absorb life force energy from the X-Man Storm, Karl Lykos has transformed once more into Sauron!
description.29: The FF take on a high impact mission to save Latveria from the wrath of Doom. Plus, Reed must face his arch nemesis in a final showdown!
description.34: Spidey's really stepped in it this time - trapped in a burning building with no way out! But luckily for the Wall-Crawler, he's not alone...LUKE CAGE is here to lend a super-strong hand!
description.35: A giant, radioactive amoeba forces the Red Guardian and the Presence to combine forces.
description.36: Howard and Beverly find themselves on another adventure to stop a mad psychiatrist. Dr. Goode is out to find out why people are claiming to have witnessed a talking duck in the area. When he discovers the preposterous claim of a talking duck is actually real...what happens next is quack-filled crazy.
description.37: An untold tale from Luke's past.  The Sandpeople attack and Luke and Biggs must save the day.
description.38: Retired 1950's super hero Comet returns to help Nova in his battle against Diamondhead!
description.42: Fall down the rabbit hole with Alice in Wonderland! Lewis Carroll's fantastical romp is given a mighty Marvel makeover in this equally surreal take on the original.
description.43: A shadowy figure is committed to slandering Spider-Man's public reputation, and they've hired the Chameleon for the job! Will J. Jonah Jameson finally have the satisfaction of watching Spider-Man fumble in a very public way? And will Peter be able to reconcile his feelings for Betty Brant? Witness the Chameleon at his villainous best!
description.44: The Avengers are dead. Korvac stands victorious. Who will stand in the god-like being's way?
description.45: The Red Skull has taken full control over the S.H.I.E.L.D. helicarrier. With Captain America on the run from a horde of Red Skulls and Col. Nick Fury facing certain death, it looks like this may be the end for America greatest soldiers!
description.48: It's a battle across New York City between the Defenders and their imposters! Hellcat's fury on the NYC subway shocks everyone. Valkyrie's team finds Nighthawk and has a memorable trip aboard the Staten Island Ferry. Is this enough excitement for the new members to stick around?
description.50: Carol's search for her missing friend Sharon takes a dire turn when she's attacked by the Lizard People!
description.53: After discovering Prime Computer and the three New Folk, Devil Dinosaur finds himself imprisoned with Stone-Hand and Eev. But why is Devil such a threat to Prime Computer? This issue is a re-telling of the Garden of Eden fable, set in Valley of the Flame!
description.54: Johnny Blaze’s soul is up for grabs by the Bounty Hunter!
description.55: Before Tony Stark can become Iron Man the Ani-Men attack!
description.57: Red dons Thor's Belt of Strength and engages in battle with the Mighty Thunderer! A surprising individual intervenes.
description.58: The original Marvel bullpen as members of the Fantastic Four! In this tongue-in-cheek edition of What If?, Stan Lee, Sol Brodsky, Flo Steinberg, and Jack Kirby become teammates in one of Marvel's most iconic series. Many inside jokes ensue.
description.59: Following their battle with Magneto, Phoenix and Beast seem to be the only survivors left!
description.60: The Fantastic Four and Zorba crash the coronation of Dr. Doom's son- Victor von Doom II! Will the FF and the Lavterian Resistance take down a tyrant?
description.70: When a nefarious bounter hunter mistakes another teenager for Skywalker, a battle ensues!
description.71: Spider-Man rises from the ashes following his fiery dispute with White Dragon! Will Spider-Man be able to take down the crime overlord once and for all? Plus, Peter Parker's college graduation!
description.72: The Avengers draw closer to discovering Korvac's whereabouts! Will Earth's Mightiest Heroes and the Guardians of the Galaxy be able to defeat this deadly enemy?
description.73: Desperate to prove he's more than what the Super Soldier serum made him, Captain America faces off against Impact 739, an S.H.I.E.L.D. training robot. But things take a turn for the worse when the Red Skull appears! Can Cap survive the Red Skull's ambush?
description.74: Robin Hood and his band of Merry Men leap off the page in this adaptation of their legends from Sherwood Forest! Maid Marian, Little John, Friar Tuck, the Sheriff of Nottingham-all your favorites are here!
description.76: The fallout of T'challa's last battle has left the Wakandan king with all-new powers - including ESP!
description.78: With villains on the loose committing crimes in the Defenders' names, the team must split into groups to defeat the imposters once and for all. But when the police can't decide who's a hero and who's a villain, all bets of victory are off!
description.81: Nova learns that his old enemy the Corruptor is leader of the Inner Circle! Meanwhile, the Rider family is shocked at Richard's long-kept secret.
description.82: Drax the Destroyer is on a rampage! His target - Captain Marvel. But why is Drax so intent on killing Mar-Vell?
description.83: Enter the Dragon! Peter gets more than he bargained for when he mettles in the personal life of lab partner, Phillip Chang. To which shadowy organization is Phillip aligned? And will Chang be able to escape the Hong Kong underground in New York's Chinatown? Plus, Betty Brant inserts herself back in Peter's life!
description.84: With the Collector defeated, Earth's Mightiest Heroes return to Earth and plan their next step to find Korvac.
description.85: This issue-A Captain America you've never seen before! The secret of Captain America's other life finally revealed!
description.86: The Purple Man has control of Daredevil's most dangerous adversaries, who Daredevil must fight to save Heather Glenn from her demise!
description.87: Stone-Hand saves Eev of the Forest-Folk after she is attacked by Sky Demons. The rescue leads to Stone-Hand's deep infatuation with Eev and he claims her as wife. Moon-Boy attempts to flee the space carrier of the Sky Demons.
description.88: Doc Samson makes a psychiatric breakthrough and discovers that Banner and the Hulk are two separate beings! Will Doc be able to crack the conundrum of Hulk's split psyche?
description.89: In an attempt to revive Unicorn, Tony brings him to Avengers Mansion.
description.90: Thor battles Loki and Red in Jotunheim to avenge Balder's death!
description.91: Still without his powers, Dracula must use his cunning to stay alive!
description.92: With the X-Men all prisoner in his Antarctic base, Magneto renews his acts of terror on the human world!
description.93: Mister Fantastic joins forces with the Latverian Freedom Fighters to stop Victor von Doom! You'll never expect this ending!
description.99: Ben and Captain America are aided by the Man-Thing against Victorious, all for possession of the Cosmic Cube!

1.text: While Luke Cage meets with Jeryn Hogarth to discuss his Hero for Hire business, Danny Rand visits Joy Meachum with a proposition of his own. Afterwards, Power Man and Iron Fist stop a bank robbery! And new criminal “The Incinerator", poses a fiery threat!

2.text: Check out legend Jack Kirby's final issue on Machine Man!

13.text: A normal bank heist thwarting turns south when Spidey is confronted by the mysterious new villain CARRION!

15.text: A change of pace: Shang-Chi gets a day off to reflect on his place in life, including Juliette's shocking admission.

18.text: Kidnapped - by Kiber the Cruel! Held captive by enemy agents, T'Challa must use all his cunning to stage an escape and reach his cousin Khanata before it's too late!

19.text: The team returns to their home turf. The Destroyer gains status with the Invaders.

20.text: Mar-Vell and Drax the Destroyer find nothing but complications on the planet Titan!

21.text: The curse of the Immortal Man! Spider-Woman meets Samuel Davis, a former soldier cursed with immortality. Despite violent attempts at suicide, Davis remains a condemned man. How can Jessica save a person whose only wish is death? And when her life is up for exchange, will Jessica take the bait?

22.text: Daredevil infiltrates the Avengers mansion and confronts the Black Widow!

30.text: A night out at the disco becomes a mind-warping affair when Peter and friends are treated to the musical samplings of Hypno-Hustler!

33.text: Super-powered Kree warrior, Captain Marvel, joins the Thing to take down Planet Kral’s Racket Boss.

38.text: Retired 1950's super hero Comet returns to help Nova in his battle against Diamondhead!

39.text: Murder Mansion…with a name this inviting, spy master Black Jack Tarr and Shang-Chi have no choice but to enter! What deadly traps lie in wait?

46.text: Machine Man enters his most dangerous fray yet…with back up to boot!

47.text: Thor deems Union Jack worthy, bestowing the British hero with the power of lightening itself. An electrifying read!

48.text: It's a battle across New York City between the Defenders and their imposters! Hellcat's fury on the NYC subway shocks everyone. Valkyrie's team finds Nighthawk and has a memorable trip aboard the Staten Island Ferry. Is this enough excitement for the new members to stick around?

50.text: Carol's search for her missing friend Sharon takes a dire turn when she's attacked by the Lizard People!

51.text: The corrupt Senator Wyatt is harboring secrets about Pyrotechnics Inc., and Jessica’s determined to uncover the truth! How was her father Jonathan Drew killed? And when the senator embroils Spider-Woman in an explosive plot, will S.H.I.E.L.D. backup arrive in time?

52.text: Spider-Man and Moon Knight fail to defeat Cyclone, the villain who had ties to the Maggia organization. Spider-Man agrees to help Moon Knight find the head mob boss, but not without reservations. Plus, Spider-Man gets a peek inside the mysterious mansion of Steven Grant!

62.text: The fate of Olympus is at stake, and it’s up to the Thing and Hercules to save the day.  But is the combined strength of the Ever-Lovin' Blue-Eyed Thing and the Prince of Power enough to take down Manduu the Merciless and Krokarr the Cruel?

64.text: Doctor Strange's astral form travels to Namor in Atlantis asking for his friend's help against Alaric...who has stolen an ancient Atlantean sword meant to kill the Sorcerer Supreme!

65.text: After surviving a car crash and saving Misty’s life, Power Man reunites with Iron Fist! The two pursue Nightshade to her headquarters and find an entire army of robots waiting to pounce! Power Man and Iron Fist enter the fray with ‘unleashed death machines’!

66.text: With Peter Spaulding as his human ally, will Machine Man be able to win the court of public opinion?

67.text: Shang-Chi faces three deadly combatants in a Battle Royale before a final matchup with Skull-Crusher!

76.text: The fallout of T'challa's last battle has left the Wakandan king with all-new powers - including ESP!

77.text: Hitler summons Thor from his native Asgard...to a hidden bunker in Third Reich Germany!

78.text: With villains on the loose committing crimes in the Defenders' names, the team must split into groups to defeat the imposters once and for all. But when the police can't decide who's a hero and who's a villain, all bets of victory are off!

79.text: Spider-Woman’s in dire straits! Defenseless against the magic of Morgan le Fay, Jessica finds that the captive Magnus is unable to help. But the nightmare’s just beginning…Jack Russell's transformed into Werewolf by Night, and Jessica’s no closer to finding the Darkhold Morgan desires!

80.text: Moon Knight follows a criminal named Lindy to prevent an assassination by the Maggia. Meanwhile, Spider-Man encounters one of Moon Knight’s multiple identities, Jack Lockley. Will Spider-Man and Moon Knight cooperate long enough to stop the Maggia from perpetrating more violence? As both heroes have opposing moral codes, this “team-up” is sure to bring conflict!

81.text: Nova learns that his old enemy the Corruptor is leader of the Inner Circle! Meanwhile, the Rider family is shocked at Richard's long-kept secret.

82.text: Drax the Destroyer is on a rampage! His target - Captain Marvel. But why is Drax so intent on killing Mar-Vell?

86.text: The Purple Man has control of Daredevil's most dangerous adversaries, who Daredevil must fight to save Heather Glenn from her demise!

95.text: With Kogar in attendance, Shang-Chi has his final battle with Shen Kuei…A.K.A. the Cat!
